 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align dashboard and alternate renderers with snapshot and attention sections","description":"Align the TUI dashboard and alternate renderer flows with the same snapshot and attention section model. This task exists because the dashboard should share the robot mental model rather than presenting a separate worldview that only coincidentally overlaps.","design":"The work should decide how dashboard screens, terse output, markdown output, and TOON output consume shared sections, summary metadata, and diagnostics or explainability affordances. It should explicitly preserve legitimate UI-specific affordances while preventing them from becoming a separate semantic branch, so human operators can answer why questions without diverging from machine-consumable semantics.

The result should be that snapshot and attention are conceptually recognizable everywhere.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when dashboard and alternate renderer experiences clearly reuse the shared section model and no longer depend on divergent state assembly paths.","notes":"Parity here improves operator ergonomics for both human and machine users, because it makes the product's mental model consistent.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:12:25.509728143Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dashboard","parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.434476151Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:11.967287453Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:12.536297631Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:36.951777963Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.7.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:44:52.669593523Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:24.335450017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":368,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","author":"codex","text":"Plan-space refinement: 8.2 now waits on 7.3 because dashboard and alternate renderer parity should consume registry-backed summary metadata and drill-down hints, not invent another UI-local semantic layer. Preserve UI-specific affordances, but keep the meaning anchored in shared metadata.","created_at":"2026-03-26T19:45:32Z"},{"id":375,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.2","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after plan-space audit: dashboard and alternate-renderer parity are a core operator experience, not a nice-to-have. Once 6.5 and 7.3 land, this should move immediately so human-facing views stop drifting from the shared robot semantics before validation freezes them.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:08:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align SSE and WebSocket behavior with durable attention semantics","description":"Align server-side streaming transports with the same durable attention semantics used elsewhere. This task exists because once attention and digest become restart-safe operator primitives, streaming transports must stop inventing their own event meanings.","design":"The work should ensure SSE and WebSocket streams honor the same cursor, replay, resync, degraded-state, request-correlation, idempotency, aggregation, cooldown, resurfacing, operator-attention-state, action-handoff, and recoverable-error semantics as CLI and REST consumers. It should also decide how stream initialization, backlog replay, and handoff to live updates behave when items are pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. This task is about semantic alignment, not merely plumbing bytes over a socket.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when streaming transports can be treated as alternative delivery mechanisms for the same durable, deduplicated, operator-shaped, and request-correlated event product rather than as bespoke feeds.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:25.318193079Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:14:48.789979612Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","robot-redesign","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:34.759084751Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:51.524008109Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:00.515239538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:37.977760883Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:53.634972268Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:35.335495935Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:13.032379944Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:44.380223071Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:03.926006101Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:08.573117873Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:25.318193079Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:36.107092492Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":338,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: SSE and WebSocket parity now explicitly covers heartbeats, filtered subscriptions, replay-to-live handoff, liveness deadlines, backpressure or boundedness markers, and consistent meaning for quiet periods.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:04Z"},{"id":355,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Sensitivity follow-up: SSE and WebSocket parity must prove that streaming and replay handoff preserve the same disclosure-control behavior as CLI and REST, including no-leak guarantees for safe previews and redaction markers.","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:24Z"},{"id":377,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","author":"codex","text":"Priority raised to P1 after plan-space audit: streaming parity is a user-facing contract and a disclosure boundary, not secondary plumbing. Once 4.8 and 8.1 are done, SSE and WebSocket should converge before validation or docs treat the redesign as finished.","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:09:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9","title":"robot-redesign/validation: tests, docs, transition, and legacy cleanup","description":"Add the deterministic fixtures, unit tests, schema goldens, integration coverage, Go-based E2E drivers, benchmark regressions, documentation refresh, transition notes, and legacy-path removal needed to make the redesign durable instead of aspirational. This epic exists because contract-heavy work only becomes real when behavior is pinned down, debugging is practical, cost regressions are visible, and the old assembly paths are retired safely.","design":"The redesign will touch contracts, SQLite persistence, event replay, explainability, renderers, and multiple transports. That means we need: checked-in example payloads and scenario matrices; shared deterministic Go test harnesses and fault injectors under testdata; package-local _test.go unit suites; integration coverage for persistence, degraded recovery, restart safety, and diagnostic evidence flow; Go-based E2E drivers under e2e/ that exercise CLI, REST, and streaming parity with verbose logging of commands, cursors, schema IDs, source_health, incidents, explainability handles, and assertion diffs; benchmark and regression coverage for payload size, latency, diagnostics cost, and storage churn; and explicit cleanup of superseded paths.

This epic is where we force the new architecture to become the only architecture, rather than one more parallel layer.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when deterministic Go-based unit, integration, benchmark, and E2E coverage pin the redesign's contract, ergonomics, explainability, and cost profile with great detailed logging; repository docs are self-contained and point to the example corpus and test entry points; and legacy robot assembly paths have been removed so the shared projection architecture is the only supported path.","notes":"Do not declare success early just because the new snapshot output looks good once. The bar is parity, restart safety, contract stability, comprehensive automated verification, and removal of redundant logic. Validation beads are part of the architecture, not optional QA garnish.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:13.892254319Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:12:54.073288880Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:13.892254319Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":321,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: the cleanup work is part of the feature, not optional janitorial follow-up.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:14Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add schema goldens and contract stability tests","description":"Add golden tests and contract stability checks for robot payload schemas, checked-in example payloads, and registry-backed discovery output. This task exists because the redesign only improves long-term quality if contract drift becomes obvious and explainable.","design":"The tests should pin checked-in schema artifacts, normative example payloads and scenario transcripts, registry-generated capabilities/help/schema views, representative payload shapes for core surfaces, canonical error or remediation examples for invalid cursor, resync-required, bounded-result, duplicate-request, and invalid-inspect conditions, request identity or idempotency examples, correlated actuation outcomes, operator-attention-state examples such as acknowledge or snooze or pin transitions, and diagnostic explainability examples such as explanation-handle shapes, evidence summaries, suppression markers, and why-this-is-stale or truncated flows. They should make breaking changes explicit, keep additive changes disciplined, and log schema IDs, example names, changed sections, error codes, request or outcome IDs, operator-state markers, diagnostic handles, and high-signal diffs when goldens move. The focus is not on testing every field serializer in isolation; it is on safeguarding the declared contract and its concrete examples.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when schema, example, and discovery drift trigger obvious test failures with rich diagnostics, and maintainers can evolve the robot contract only through explicit intentional updates to schemas and examples, including retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-override semantics.","notes":"Use the example corpus as an executable contract, not as a bag of arbitrary snapshots.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:26.297471362Z","created_